recipes.title: Helles Lager
recipes.notes:
Mash and recirculate 60 minutes at 149°F (62°C) with a mash thickness of 1.5 qt.

4g of yeast nutrient to boil.

Ferment at 55°F, Lager at 34.

recipes.title: Sierra Nevada Pale Ale Clone
recipes.author: Beerfan
recipes.notes:
if your like me and love hops just add an ounce of Cascade to your keg, let it slow carbonate for a 3 or 4 days then take it out and enjoy a great beer! 

Adjust your caramel 60L and shoot for an SRM of 8.

recipes.title: Zwickelbier
recipes.author: Bryant
recipes.notes:
ALCOHOL BY VOLUME:	 	5.2%
HOP BITTERNESS (IBU):	 	19
COLOR:	 	Golden Yellow
OG:	 	12.0 Plato
HOPS:	 	Hallertau Perle, Hallertau Mittelfrueh
MALTS:	 	Pilsner, Caramel

Mashing: Single decoction mash. Mash in at 122 deg F, increase temperature and rest at 144 deg F. Pull the decoction mash and boil decoction for 30 min. Transfer decoction mash back to main mash, targeting 162 deg F of combined mash after decoction mash gets pumped back. Rest at 162 deg F.
Boil: Boil for 90 min.
Hops: Hallertauer Tradition Hallertauer Mittelfrueh. Target BU: 19
Hop Additions: Add 75% of total amount at the start of the boil. Add 25% of total amount at the end of the boil.
Yeast: Bavarian Lager Yeast
Fermentation Profile: Ferment cold (45 – 52 deg F target). Mature at 32 – 34 deg F for 3 – 4 weeks

recipes.title: Witchcraft
recipes.notes:
All grains and pumpkin go in the mash.  If the pumpkin is in the boil you will most likely lose a gallon of water, and have a tough time straining the pumpkin out.

If you really want to put the pumpkin into the boil then you should use a grain bag or filter the wort before racking to your primary.

The pumpkin should be cleaned and cut into small cubes and baked for 45 mins at 350, then mashed and coated with honey.  Then baked for another 45 mins at 350. Let it cool to 154 and add to mash.

For the vanilla bean vodka solution, two vanilla beans are cut in half.  The seeds and goodies are then scraped into 4oz of vodka. Let the vodka sit for two weeks.
